Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.34,0:00:10.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Reverse, all stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.79,0:00:18.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.79,0:00:21.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,For now, it doesn't look \Nlike there's any danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.19,0:00:23.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But are we really gonna be okay after this?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.88,0:00:28.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, sure. That tin can \Nwipe out the whalesquid.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.79,0:00:31.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,D-Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:38.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Tin can! Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.50,0:00:42.03,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.97,0:00:47.35,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Confirmed: All Hideauze inhabiting this \Narea of the ocean have been exterminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.35,0:00:49.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Great job!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.95,0:00:52.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Get out the Yunboros!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.54,0:00:55.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The legendary treasure is ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.18,0:00:57.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.01,0:02:52.01,Signs,,0000,0000,0000,,Island of Ambition
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.48,0:02:58.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.34,0:03:00.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The shaft is over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.14,0:03:04.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead! Take it slow!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.06,0:03:07.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.37,0:03:09.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! We're okay over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.84,0:03:11.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion! Come here a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:12.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.16,0:03:22.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This looks promising, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.74,0:03:23.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.30,0:04:28.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Bro...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.50,0:04:31.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to drink this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.64,0:04:40.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.22,0:04:45.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think? And this \Nis just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.27,0:04:48.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the grand legacy of our ancestors!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.74,0:04:54.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yep. There's even more incredible treasure \Nwaitin' deep inside the whalesquid nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.57,0:04:57.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's just like my big brother said.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.35,0:05:02.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not rotted out at all. And there's an \Nunlimited supply at the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.37,0:05:06.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it, the treasure that will bring \Nthe former civilization back to the world!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.05,0:05:09.27,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Restoring the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.27,0:05:12.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the ones that found \Nit! So it's {\i1}our{\i0} treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.90,0:05:14.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you saying?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.82,0:05:19.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought we could use this legacy to enrich \Nthe lives of as many people as possible!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.17,0:05:22.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's the point of the whole damn thing \Nunless we enrich our own lives first?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.27,0:05:25.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we keep it to ourselves, people \Nwill show up to try and steal it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.07,0:05:29.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got tons of weapons and ammo! \NThere ain't nothin' to be afraid of!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.61,0:05:31.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not the issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.36,0:05:33.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll sink anybody that gets close to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.34,0:05:35.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Send out a radio message!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.47,0:05:39.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Spread the word that the whalesquid have \Nbeen annihilated and that we got the treasure!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.06,0:05:41.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We can't! It would only stir \Nup other ships in the area!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.07,0:05:44.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a {\i1}warning{\i0} for them to stay away!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.40,0:05:47.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're gonna send it out as far and \Nwide as possible! Get it ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.67,0:05:54.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a message to all \Nships that can hear this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.76,0:05:59.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We wiped out all the whalesquid that \Nwere livin' in the Sea of Mist!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:01.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,All the pods, all the nests, everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.37,0:06:06.84,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is Pinion! Remember me \Nas Pinion of the Sea of Mist!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.32,0:06:12.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Any bastards out there after the whalesquid \Nnest treasure, you're too damn late!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.40,0:06:15.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get any funny ideas!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.49,0:06:18.83,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The treasure is all ours!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.24,0:06:25.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a warning to all ships! Any boats \Nthat get close will be sunk without mercy!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.55,0:06:29.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Pinion has a valid point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.64,0:06:31.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even you?! What's going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:35.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That being said, I'm sure pirates will \Ntarget us. We'll need to prepare for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.66,0:06:38.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why do we have to assume \Nthat we're going to battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.86,0:06:40.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Flange!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.96,0:06:42.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You have a package.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.90,0:06:44.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.17,0:06:50.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.58,0:06:56.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.73,0:07:01.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that Ledo killed \Nall the whalesquid...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.51,0:07:03.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. It's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:06.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Are we going to be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.24,0:07:09.07,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.55,0:07:12.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you agree with all this, Mr. Flange?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.94,0:07:12.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.53,0:07:14.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.31,0:07:24.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,With Ledo and Chamber around, we can \Nsearch deep into the whalesquid nest.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.42,0:07:25.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm fine with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.23,0:07:30.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But not even trading what we \Nbring up with other ships,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.01,0:07:33.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,and spouting threats to \Nattack if they draw near...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.89,0:07:38.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't stop him?! At this rate, \Nwe'll be treated as outcasts!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.43,0:07:42.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The shipmasters that I led \Nhave begun to follow Pinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.00,0:07:50.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Certainly, making use of the salvage \Nrequires his skills as a repairman.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.82,0:07:52.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's little that \Ncan be done to stop him.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.98,0:07:54.92,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.01,0:08:19.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ensign.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.54,0:08:24.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Why aren't you givin' us a hand?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.99,0:08:28.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take care of the salvage yourselves!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.12,0:08:32.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The shaft is blocked up with salvage. \NI want the tin can to move the stuff!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.77,0:08:33.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.45,0:08:38.24,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with you, Ledo?! \NWhat're you afraid of?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.73,0:08:40.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Afraid? Me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.91,0:08:41.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Go to hell!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.48,0:08:46.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I annihilated the Hideauze! I fear nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.96,0:08:48.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I fear...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.40,0:09:02.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Joe, let's hang it up for the day!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.68,0:09:03.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.16,0:09:18.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, has the reorganization \Nlayout been finalized?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.87,0:09:22.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. The shipmasters were very cooperative.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.30,0:09:25.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Now all we need to do is \Nreset the interlocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:27.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Though it's a major undertaking...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.45,0:09:31.42,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fleet Commander, have you \Nheard Pinion's broadcast?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.22,0:09:34.05,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.05,0:09:36.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think, frankly speaking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.78,0:09:41.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Until we have any factual evidence for \Nhis claims, there's no need to respond.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.61,0:09:42.87,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.27,0:09:45.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Has word already spread across the fleet?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.40,0:09:47.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,There's likely not a single \Nsoul who doesn't know about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.67,0:09:48.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.45,0:09:54.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Of the shipmasters who believe it, there may \Nbe some who are envious and wish to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.11,0:09:56.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And if there are?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.14,0:10:00.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll respect their wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.13,0:10:07.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Dr. Oldham, is it true that Ledo \Ndestroyed a nest of whalesquid?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.72,0:10:11.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. That's what Pinion \Nsaid on a radio broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.79,0:10:13.53,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.25,0:10:16.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.74,0:10:18.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What a stupid thing to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.34,0:10:34.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I swore I'd get revenge for my big brother...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.68,0:10:38.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You said it was just a dream, remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.41,0:10:48.75,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.32,0:10:51.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope Melty's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.89,0:10:56.30,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It's alright, right? After all, \Nit's only Pinion talking...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.06,0:10:59.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, Amy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.93,0:11:02.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How would I know about that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.15,0:11:04.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.46,0:11:09.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo... Why...?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.84,0:11:30.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do they look like they're gonna surrender?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.49,0:11:33.40,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,No. But they're probably out of ammo.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.40,0:11:34.54,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep attacking.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.54,0:11:35.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.73,0:11:38.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We've got plenty of ammunition left.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.05,0:11:42.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, they started it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.69,0:11:44.13,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're telling us to sink them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.13,0:11:46.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unless they put both hands up first...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.20,0:11:50.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's right! Repairs on the \Ntreasure should be done by now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.16,0:11:52.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's try it on 'em!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.71,0:11:55.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.32,0:11:58.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:12:00.50,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay. Good enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:04.44,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything's set!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.44,0:12:06.71,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.88,0:12:11.14,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,"Fire", he says...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.14,0:12:13.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This one? Or this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.63,0:12:25.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doin'?! You got lousy aim!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.66,0:12:27.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They're radioing that they surrender!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.10,0:12:29.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Shoulda done that before, dumbasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.45,0:12:36.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeesh. You wasted time and ammo.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.47,0:12:42.82,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You got some guts pickin' a fight with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.43,0:12:47.99,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, help us!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.36,0:12:51.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll give you all our cargo, \Njust let us join up with you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.71,0:12:55.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If we accepted every plea like that,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.20,0:12:56.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,this place would get huge...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.75,0:13:02.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait a second. If the fleet expands \Nlike this, we'll be invincible.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.18,0:13:06.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And there's no end to the stuff \Nwe can raise from the sea bottom.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.64,0:13:09.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright! Anybody that wants to can \Nbring your things and come over!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.76,0:13:11.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.22,0:13:13.68,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Old man, we've come to an agreement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.52,0:13:18.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, lock this guy up somewhere!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.10,0:13:31.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Ledo...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.17,0:13:39.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I want the tin can to check \Nout the stuff we salvaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.98,0:13:45.80,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.15,0:13:51.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The ensign's permission is required \Nfor anything outside of military duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.93,0:13:53.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, fine. It's okay, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.73,0:13:56.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Do what you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.85,0:13:59.90,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then we're good to go! Follow me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.27,0:14:03.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do it without you!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.16,0:14:05.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You too, tin can top dog! Let's go!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.43,0:14:18.95,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Come on, drink!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Good work, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.62,0:14:33.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When a ship picked a fight with us, we \Nmade it fly the white flag in no time!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.16,0:14:39.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The wind of fortune's been blowin' on us \Never since we made this our base of operations!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.61,0:14:42.77,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's all thanks to Ledo and Chamber!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.77,0:14:46.65,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Everyone, kiss this tin \Ncan's ass in gratitude!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.95,0:15:08.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.35,0:15:11.72,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What am I doing it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.94,0:15:16.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I doing it for?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.15,0:15:19.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When did it start?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.84,0:15:22.52,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,When I first became conscious \Nin this strange land?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.97,0:15:28.97,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or the first time I got inside \NChamber... this Machine Caliber?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.24,0:15:32.00,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Or since I was born?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.42,0:15:44.32,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.32,0:15:46.47,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a rudimentary electromagnetic weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.47,0:15:48.86,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Electromagnetic? What the hell is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.12,0:15:53.98,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Its basic structure is no different than \Nthe beam armament that I am equipped with.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.98,0:15:55.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Seriously?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.48,0:16:00.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I estimate its power \Noutput to be 1/50th of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.73,0:16:03.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even 1/50th of your power is a big deal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.02,0:16:09.91,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Its power output is approximately 76 times \Ngreater than that of this whole fleet.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.91,0:16:13.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright, alright! Is this thing still usable?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:17.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is possible to restore its \Nfunctions through repairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:21.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,However, a great amount of electricity \Nis required to operate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.12,0:16:22.79,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Electricity, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.25,0:16:26.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Would it work if we harnessed the lightbugs?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.35,0:16:28.04,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That hypothesis requires investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.04,0:16:31.51,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Then do it! I'll go tell Ledo!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.34,0:17:06.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have discovered evidence to back \Nup the Hideauze video recording.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:08.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is the lightbugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.22,0:17:14.34,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Lightbugs are nanomachines and actually\N comprise the Hideauze shell.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.68,0:17:19.60,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,They absorb electromagnetic waves and \Ntransform them into energy with high efficiency.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.60,0:17:24.09,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,At the same time, they are self-replicating \Nand through carbon bonding,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.09,0:17:27.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,function as a durable exoskeleton.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.22,0:17:32.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,This is proof that the Hideauze are the \Nresults of directed evolution by the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.97,0:17:33.48,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.07,0:17:36.64,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be like this?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.64,0:17:42.02,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though it thoroughly refutes the meaning \Nof the Galactic Alliance's... of {\i1}my{\i0} battle!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.55,0:17:45.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You recognize an error in your knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.89,0:17:54.01,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I fight the Hideauze if \Nthey're the evolved human race?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.01,0:17:57.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a point to fighting them?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.51,0:18:00.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If not, then I can't fight!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.43,0:18:05.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't murder those creatures...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.83,0:18:07.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.77,0:18:12.57,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Your cognition refutes the \Nsignificance of our existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.81,0:18:17.63,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You saw them too, didn't you?! The \Nforms of newborn whalesquid...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.19,0:18:20.59,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,We're the same human race and \Nwe're killing each other!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.59,0:18:23.56,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the true nature of our war!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.56,0:18:25.62,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Even after obtaining this information,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.62,0:18:29.29,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,there is no reason to give up \Non annihilating the Hideauze.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.85,0:18:31.46,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That's only you!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.16,0:18:34.55,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But for me...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.50,0:18:40.66,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative. The Hideauze bring fundamental \Ndestruction to the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.66,0:18:44.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Helping to avoid that is your sole mission.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:46.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we're all humans!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.77,0:18:49.19,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough of the Alliance's brainwashing!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.01,0:18:55.26,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Negative. The parallel link between \Nthe Alliance and myself has been lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.26,0:19:00.15,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I have arrived at this conclusion \Nindependently, based on information analysis.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.26,0:19:02.37,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.37,0:19:06.73,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The human race and the Hideauze will always \Nbe antagonistic toward one another.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.73,0:19:11.49,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The reason for this is they are beings who \Nhave rejected civilization as a whole.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.04,0:19:14.22,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.46,0:19:20.43,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If the human race were equipped with strong, \Nversatile bodies like the Hideauze,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.43,0:19:24.93,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it would not have been necessary \Nto develop Machine Calibers.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.20,0:19:29.17,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,My system is the crystallization of \Nthe intelligence of the human race.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.17,0:19:35.23,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But we are also necessary to \Noffset the fragile human body.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.77,0:19:38.88,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Conjecture: Humans are beings \Nthat surpass their own limits,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.88,0:19:43.76,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,develop their intellect, \Nand build civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.22,0:19:49.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The existence of civilization is what separates \Nthe human race from all other primates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.95,0:19:56.08,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the Hideauze have thrown away their \Nhuman forms and have no physical limits.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.08,0:20:00.12,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,If living beings only seek out \Nhappiness and gratification,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.12,0:20:03.89,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,it isn't necessary for them \Nto have a higher intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.77,0:20:10.06,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,But the human race relies \Nsolely on Machine Calibers.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.06,0:20:14.96,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,That is to say, we are the crystallization \Nof pure intellect, a product of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.40,0:20:19.69,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And by overcoming even that \Nintellect, the Hideauze
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.69,0:20:23.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,have reached an extreme state of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.77,0:20:27.28,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying the Hideauze \Nare an extreme life form.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.85,0:20:30.78,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, you and I
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.78,0:20:34.16,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,must battle, with the dignity \Nof the human race at stake.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.72,0:20:40.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,In a war with something that shares \Nthe same building blocks as you,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.74,0:20:43.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,failure means certain extinction.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:48.11,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,One side seeks out civilization. \NThe other abandons it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.37,0:20:51.67,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,The war between the Galactic Alliance \Nof Humankind and the Hideauze
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.67,0:20:55.18,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,is a conflict between two \Ndifferent survival strategies,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.18,0:20:57.81,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,one in which being culled is all \Nthat waits for the losing side.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.56,0:20:59.94,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Culled...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.79,0:21:04.74,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as you wish to exist, you \Ndon't have the luxury of a choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.17,0:21:07.70,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Fight and impose our ways?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:11.20,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,A machine like you is \Ntelling a human like me...?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.43,0:21:15.41,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,I am a Pilot Support Enlightenment \NInterface System.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.05,0:21:21.38,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,By achieving more and more results, you \Nwill realize the importance of existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.73,0:21:30.36,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Receiving polarized photon sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.36,0:21:33.31,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a Galactic Alliance standard \Nencrypted communication wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.82,0:21:35.10,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.59,0:21:37.39,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Identified as an allied mech.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.39,0:21:38.61,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Allied mech?!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.53,0:22:08.21,Main Dialog,,0000,0000,0000,,Commander Kugel...
